{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":{"name":"Anubhav Srivastava","contacts":{"twitter":"onlyanubhav"}},"disqusShortname":"theanubhav","subtitle":"Personal quick tips for Web Developers","title":"Quick Dev tips by Anubhav Srivastava","url":"http://devtips.theanubhav.com"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1a9f8225-15ce-5b9f-b3b2-c5bad03c2e17","html":"<p>This is a series of libraries and utilities for building Command-line-interfaces aka CLI using Node.js and ecosystem around it. Similar utilities/helpers may be available for other languages but, these series is focused on JavaScript and its friends.</p>\n<p>You can check all articles under <a href=\"/category/cli-build-tool/\"><code class=\"language-text\">CLI Build Tool</code></a> tag.</p>\n<h2 id=\"meow\"><a href=\"#meow\" aria-label=\"meow permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/meow\">meow</a></h2>\n<p>If you are building a CLI that has some command line options (args e.g ‚Äîversion), sometimes mandatory and usually optional, <code class=\"language-text\">meow</code> is the library you should be banking on. Built by sindresorhus, which adds a lot of credibility to this library, is nearly used by 1.5+ million other packages.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">meow</code> is the easiest way to write command line apps with arguments for Node.js.</p>\n<h3 id=\"default-arg-parsing\"><a href=\"#default-arg-parsing\" aria-label=\"default arg parsing permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Default arg parsing</h3>\n<p>You do not need to worry about <code class=\"language-text\">process.argv</code> and everything around it. <code class=\"language-text\">meow</code> takes care of arguments and it casing (By default converts to CamelCase).</p>\n<h3 id=\"default-support-for---help-and---version\"><a href=\"#default-support-for---help-and---version\" aria-label=\"default support for   help and   version permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Default support for <code class=\"language-text\">--help</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">--version</code></h3>\n<p>It provides support for showing CLI options as help to user and also version of your app from <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> file. No extra handling is required</p>\n<h3 id=\"support-for-alias-and-descriptions\"><a href=\"#support-for-alias-and-descriptions\" aria-label=\"support for alias and descriptions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Support for alias and descriptions</h3>\n<p>You can add alias for long argument options, like ‚Äîhelp can be -h.</p>\n<p>All flags and values are available in meow instance, which can be used by the CLI for acting on it.</p>\n<p>You can check out official <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/meow\">repo</a> for all usage details.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0632dcce33011dabb3d67a477d4c6184/4db5f/blamenetmeow.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100.33670033670035%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Screenshot\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0632dcce33011dabb3d67a477d4c6184/f570d/blamenetmeow.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0632dcce33011dabb3d67a477d4c6184/0783d/blamenetmeow.png 240w,\n/static/0632dcce33011dabb3d67a477d4c6184/782f4/blamenetmeow.png 480w,\n/static/0632dcce33011dabb3d67a477d4c6184/f570d/blamenetmeow.png 960w,\n/static/0632dcce33011dabb3d67a477d4c6184/4db5f/blamenetmeow.png 1188w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>Github Repo: <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/meow\">meow</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"---other-module-yargs---\"><a href=\"#---other-module-yargs---\" aria-label=\"   other module yargs    permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><!-- other module yargs --></h2>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/cli-meow","tagSlugs":["/tag/cli/","/tag/tools/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-06-23T18:05:00.738Z","description":"Node.js CLI App helper module for argument parsing","tags":["CLI","Tools"],"title":"Tool of the Trade for CLI Apps - `Meow` üêà"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/cli-meow"}}